H0.text: Aerobic respiration is a function found in both prokaryotic and eukaryotic cells, which together make up all living things.

H1.text: Sexual reproduction is the function found in both prokaryotic and eukaryotic cells.

H2.text: Protein production is the function found in both prokaryotic and eukaryotic cells, the two types of cells that make up all living things.

H3.text: Nitrogen fixation is a function found in both prokaryotic and eukaryotic cells, as all living things are made up of prokaryotic or eukaryotic cells.

A4.text: Other non-membrane-bound organelles may be proteinaceous such as the ribosomes present (though different) in both groups.
